com.analog.lyric.options

Class OptionKeys

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<java.lang.String,IOptionKey<?>>
      • com.analog.lyric.options.OptionKeys
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Map<java.lang.String,IOptionKey<?>>

    @Immutable
public final class OptionKeys
extends java.util.AbstractMap<java.lang.String,IOptionKey<?>>
    An immutable map of option keys declared in a single class.

    This provides a way to look up related option keys by their identifier name. However, when working with keys that can declared in multiple classes, you will typically want to make use of an OptionRegistry for looking up options by name.

    This object maps simple identifier strings to IOptionKey instances declared in the declaringClass() associated with this object. This will include mappings for every publicly accessible static final fields of IOptionKey that refer to a "canonical instance" of the key (an instance for which OptionKey.getCanonicalInstance(com.analog.lyric.options.IOptionKey<T>) returns the instance itself).

    Instances are obtained using declaredInClass(Class).
